        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_ærx" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ærx</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ærxæ</orth></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>балка</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>beam</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>лощина</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>hollow</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>высохшее русло</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>dry wash</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>размытые рекой или дождевыми потоками места</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>places that were degraded by river of by rain flows</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>qæwy æddæ, ḱysyl ærxy æmbæxst wydysty ærtæ baræǵy sæ bæxtīmæ... k˳y
                            sæ īw, k˳y sæ īnnæ īw ærxæj rakastī æmæ īw bajq˳ysta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>за аулом в небольшой лощине укрылись три всадника с лошадьми... то
                                один, то другой из них выглядывал из лощины и прислушивался</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>there were tree horsemen with horses hiding in a small gorge behind
                                the aul… one and another of them looked out the gorge and
                                listened</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Arsen"
                            /><biblScope>77—78</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Тюрко-монгольское слово широкого распространения; ср. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>arх</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w>arq</w></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w>arəq</w>
                        <gloss><q>канал</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mn"><lang/>
                        <w>ark</w>
                        <gloss><q>ров</q></gloss></mentioned> ‘fossa’, <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><lang/>
                        <w>árok</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>arqi</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>arq</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="udi"><lang/>
                        <w>arx</w>
                        <gloss><q>ров</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="dar"><lang/>
                        <w>harq</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lez"><lang/>
                        <w>arx</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>or</w>
                        <gloss><q>канава</q></gloss></mentioned>, cр. также <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>arq</w>
                        <gloss><q>канал</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘арык’ (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Ягелло"/></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>warxa</w>
                        <gloss><q>'small channel in а field</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Morgenstierne._EVP"
                        /><biblScope>90</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ru-x-dial"><lang/>
                        <w>верх</w>
                        <gloss><q>ложбина</q></gloss></mentioned>. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="krc-x-balkar" extralang="krc-x-karachay"><lang/>
                        <w>ərxə</w>
                        <gloss><q>русло дождевого потока</q></gloss></mentioned> %bкар.%b примыкает
                    и по форме и по значению к <mentioned xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/>
                        <w>ærxæ</w></mentioned>. В более новое время это же тюркское слово было
                    вторично заимствовано в осетинский в форме <ref type="xr" target="#entry_aryq"
                    />; см. это слово.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>84</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Being of Turkic-Mongolian origin, it is widespread across
                    languages; compare <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>arх</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w>arq</w></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w>arəq</w>
                        <gloss><q>channel</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mn"><lang/>
                        <w>ark</w>
                        <gloss><q>ditch</q></gloss></mentioned> ‘fossa’, <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><lang/>
                        <w>árok</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>arqi</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>arq</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="udi"><lang/>
                        <w>arx</w>
                        <gloss><q>ditch</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="dar"><lang/>
                        <w>harq</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lez"><lang/>
                        <w>arx</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>or</w>
                        <gloss><q>drain</q></gloss></mentioned>, see also <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>arq</w>
                        <gloss><q>channel</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘irrigation ditch’ (<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Ягелло"/></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>warxa</w>
                        <gloss><q>'small channel in а field</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Morgenstierne._EVP"
                        /><biblScope>90</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ru-x-dial"><lang/> <w>verx</w>
                        <gloss><q>shallow gully</q></gloss></mentioned>. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/>
                        <w>ərxə</w>
                        <gloss><q>channel of a rain flow</q></gloss></mentioned> %bкар.%b is close
                    by form and by meaning to <mentioned xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/>
                        <w>ærxæ</w></mentioned>. The same turkic word was borrowed in Ossetic for
                    the second time in the form <ref type="xr" target="#entry_aryq"/>; see this
                            word.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>84</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
